{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated library update job for `org.mockito:mockito-core:5.0.0` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3997-library-update-request-org.mockito-mockito-core-5.0.0-5aeb4655\n\nAlthough the run was labeled `test_generation_failed`, the preserved artifacts point to `native-test-verify` as the real blocker. The metrics show no persisted patch (`generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, and the starting/ending commit both stayed at `050f471a8d4c8719a30888ab1d442188c26c2bd0`), but the native verification logs show the image was built and the generated suite then failed at runtime with missing registrations and some generated-test incompatibilities. Representative failures:\n- `cycle-35`: `MissingSerializationRegistrationError` for `org.mockito.internal.invocation.SerializableMethod`\n- `cycle-33`: `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for unsafe instantiation of `org_mockito.mockito_core.LenientCopyToolTest$Holder`\n- `cycle-31`: `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.util.stream.LongStream#empty()`\nThe native test output also shows additional failures such as `NoSuchMethodError: Method 'matches(T)' not found in ArgumentMatcher`, `ClassNotFoundException: org.mockito.internal.invocation.SerializableMethod`, and a proxy `proxyClassLookup(...)` reflection failure. The run summary reported low dynamic-access coverage as well (`49/104`, 47.12%).\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `logs/org.mockito:mockito-core:5.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-35-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T16-00-47-359882Z.log`\n- `logs/org.mockito:mockito-core:5.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-33-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T15-59-03-175188Z.log`\n- `logs/org.mockito:mockito-core:5.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-31-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T15-57-20-723518Z.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the generated native-test failures and add the missing Mockito/JDK metadata needed for serialization, proxy lookup, Optional/Stream empty helpers, and unsafe-allocation paths.\n2. Check the generated tests for Mockito 5.0.0 API drift, especially the `ArgumentMatcher.matches(T)` failures and the `SerializableMethodTest` assumptions, then adjust or replace the offending tests.\n3. Re-run the `org.mockito:mockito-core:5.0.0` flow and confirm native verification passes with improved dynamic-access coverage."}}
